After a week of my gulag fine, I was really not interested. I returned to the school. It was so hard to accept the fact that Tuymazov was fine. In my nightmare, I saw a ghost-like figure with a gun killing a man. What was he doing here?!....I looked to the black man beside me...I screamed and ran out of the room. I looked for my brother and found him. I told Tuymazov mercilessly that he was forgiven for everything he had done.

It is hard to forget. I am still wondering how I can forget all the large and small spiritual damage.

Just two months ago, I was standing in front of one of the biggest highest mountains in the world. I looked up at the gigantic giant wrapped in thickly snow. How beautiful it was from a distance! But there was too much work to do. Having changed my life at the Partonie Orphanage in 2006, Kazakhse Dave now lives in Toronto. Most of the time, I enjoy listening to gossip about celebrities and I rephrase the story to make it seem like it was me who actually said that. But all that changed in 2006 when I was asked to do the bidding of God.
